<dl id="n37009r"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n37" href="#n37009r">N37 (VI.B.28A)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n37all.htm#n37009r"> 9(r)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 326 We show all we advertise</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[<font size="-1">THE CIRCUS</font>]</font>: Barnum&apos;s programs and advance publicity began to question the honesty of other shows. One year this verse was used: &ldquo;Others may issue paper lies, / But <mark>we show all we advertise</mark>.&rdquo; <small> M.R. Werner, <a name="MRWP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MRWP"><cite title="source">P.T. Barnum</cite></a> (1923) 326</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
